In the ever-changing landscape of today's digital era, the way art is distributed has undergone significant shifts. We've moved away from the traditional methods of art consumption and physical distribution, embracing the widespread use of digital platforms. This shift not only allows artists to easily connect with a global audience but also mirrors the changing face of artistic expression in our contemporary world.\
While the global accessibility is undoubtedly beneficial for artists, it comes with its own set of challenges that require careful consideration. Tackling various obstacles, such as the complex task of tracking royalties, ensuring robust legal protection, and navigating transparency issues, becomes crucial. These challenges, though formidable, play a pivotal role in determining the path and longevity of art in this digital age.\
